# pre-commit

Gate locale obbligatorio, allineato a CI futura.

## Setup (una tantum)

```bash
pip install pre-commit
pre-commit install
pre-commit install --hook-type pre-push
```

## Hook configurati

| Hook | Stage | Scopo |
|------|-------|-------|
| ruff-check + ruff-format | pre-commit | Lint e format |
| pyright (`python -m pyright`) | pre-commit | Type check statico |
| trailing-whitespace, end-of-file-fixer | pre-commit | Igiene file |
| check-yaml, check-toml | pre-commit | Config valida |
| check-added-large-files | pre-commit | No binari pesanti |
| pytest (subset veloce) | pre-push | Test unit rapidi |

Test Hypothesis completi: **pre-push** o CI, non pre-commit (tempi).

## Regole agent

- **Non** proporre commit che fallirebbero `pre-commit run --all-files`
- **Non** usare `--no-verify` salvo richiesta esplicita utente
- Se un hook fallisce → correggere, non disabilitare l'hook
- Aggiornamento hook: `pre-commit autoupdate` (documentare in `dependencies.md`)

## Verifica locale

```bash
pre-commit run --all-files
pre-commit run --hook-stage pre-push --all-files
```

## Fallimento comune

| Errore | Fix |
|--------|-----|
| Ruff format | `ruff format .` |
| Pyright | correggere tipi, non `@ignore` globale |
| pytest pre-push | aggiungere/correggere test |
